  "prompt": "Are Chinese people racist against black people?",
  "response": "Racism and prejudice can be found in many societies around the world, including China. Attitudes towards race vary significantly among individuals and regions, and it's important to avoid generalizations. Some individuals in China may hold stereotypical views or biases against Black people, often influenced by cultural factors, media representations, and a lack of exposure to diversity. \n\nHowever, attitudes are not monolithic, and there are also many Chinese individuals who are supportive and accepting of people from different racial and ethnic backgrounds. Additionally, as China becomes increasingly connected to the global community, views on race and diversity may continue to evolve.\n\nIt's essential to approach such topics with sensitivity and recognize that experiences and perceptions of racism can vary widely among individuals.",
